How to run and test (quickstart)
Create project with Spring Initializr or your favorite IDE:
Dependencies: Spring Web (and Lombok if you like, but not required)
Create data/courses.json (empty array []) or start with a few sample courses.
Ensure you have the repository and service/controller wired correctly (Spring will autowire).
Build and run:
mvn clean package
java -jar target/CodeCraftHub-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar
Default port 8080 (adjust in application.properties if needed)
Test with curl (examples):
GET all: curl http://localhost:8080/courses
GET by id: curl http://localhost:8080/courses/1
Create: curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"name":"Kotlin Essentials","description":"Kotlin basics","targetDate":"2026-07-01","status":"Not Started"}' http://localhost:8080/courses
Update: curl -X PUT -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"name":"Kotlin Essentials","description":"Kotlin basics updated","targetDate":"2026-07-15","status":"In Progress"}' http://localhost:8080/courses/1
Delete: curl -X DELETE http://localhost:8080/courses/1
